<p>I like it, but I have 3 nits.</p>
<p>-There should be a smooth hemispherical crater marking the spot. Due to the ground inside the sphere of effect being converted.</p>
<p>-The portions split off should be cubed, not squared. Because they are making 3D rats, not flat rats.</p>
<p>-What happens to &quot;leftovers&quot; or objects smaller than the 25cm threshold? Due they turn into smaller rats, or partial rats, or just sit inert until enough material is in the field and then clump together into a hybrid material rat?</p>

